><A HREF="gc.htm"> Of God and His Creatures</a><hr><p>
It may be urged that better than rest in the perfectly understood would 
be a perpetual progress in understanding. But God in heaven never is 
perfectly understood, or comprehended, by the Blessed. Cf Chap. LXXII, 
n. 8. 

